reviewText: ANDRE IS AT HOME AND HOME LOVES HIM.  ALWAYS GOOD MUSIC, PERFORMERS, AND SURPRISES.  THE AUDANCE PERFORMS AS WELL AS ANDRE.  I ENJOY WATCHING THE PEOPLES' REACTIONS TO THE SHOW.  BEAUTIFULLY FILMED AND EDITED.  ANDRE'S MUSIC IS ALWAYS ABOUT THE SAME AND AT THE SAME TIME NEW AND ENJOYABLE.THE FIRST PART HAS TOO MUCH ORANGE COLOR BUT THAT IS OK.  AFTER ALL IT IS THEIR NATION.
summary: ANDRE AND MAASTRICT ALWAYS A GOOD COMBO
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht

reviewText: Excellent DVD. This is in his hometown & it looks as if the whole town was there having a ball. They set up tables in the town square just enjoying the music.The music is just fantastic. Would highly recomend it.
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht

reviewText: Shjpped on time as promised and in good condition. I am a violinist, formerly with the Chicago Civic Symphony and really love Andre's  music.  I only wish he would not repeat the same music on all of his recordings.
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht

reviewText: I bought this CD for a friend at church because she mentioned seeing him on TV.  I've heard this one before too and know that she will be absolutely delighted!  And it came to my house a couple days before I expected it, so that's even better yet! Good deal!
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht

reviewText: BRAVO..... BRAVO....... What more is there to say about the brilliance of this man and the talent of his Johann Strauss Orchestra? His concert settings and backdrops tend to sweep one up in the atmosphere of the location and makes you a part of the event.
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht

reviewText: I THINK THIS IS THE BEST OF THE MAASTRICHT RECORDINGS AND FOUND IT VERY ENJOYABLECLEARLY THE AUDIENCE LOVED ITTREVOR B
Title: Andre & Friends-Live in Maastricht
